{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"144512b4-f3fa-4c43-87c2-eb9c149ac87f","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a built-in MAUI ContentPage property — that's likely why it has no effect. You need platform-specific configuration:\n\n### iOS — disable safe-area insets\n\nAdd the iOS platform namespace and set `UseSafeArea=\"False\"`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n           Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n           VerticalOptions=\"Fill\"\n           HorizontalOptions=\"Fill\" />\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### Android — draw behind system bars\n\nIn your `MainActivity.cs`, override `OnCreate` to enable edge-to-edge:\n\n```csharp\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n    if (Window is not null)\n    {\n        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n        Window.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n        Window.SetNavigationBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n> **Note:** On Android 15+ (API 35), edge-to-edge is enforced by default, but you still need `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(window, false)` on older targets.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Platform | What to set |\n|----------|------------|\n| iOS | `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` on the page |\n| Android | `WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(window, false)` + transparent bars |\n| Image | `Aspect=\"AspectFill\"`, `Fill` for both layout options |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"16485676-47f2-440f-ab1d-ae801de0508d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about making content go edge-to-edge in a .NET MAUI app, going behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've tried `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` but the image still has padding.\n\nThis is a common .NET MAUI question. Let me think about what they need:\n\n1. `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on ContentPage isn't a standard MAUI API - they might be confusing it with something else, or it might be a newer API.\n\n2. In .NET MAUI, to go edge-to-edge (behind status bar and navigation bar), you typically need to:\n   - On iOS, use the `IgnoreSafeArea` property on views to push content behind the safe area\n   - On Android, set the status bar color with transparency and configure layouts to extend behind system bars\n\nThe approach varies between platforms, and newer MAUI versions have improved support for edge-to-edge displays, so I should clarify what version they're using and which platform they're targeting. the image fills the entire page with `Aspect=\"AspectFill\"`, and on Android you'll need to handle the system bars being transparent through platform-specific configuration. In .NET 9 and beyond, there are better APIs for managing edge-to-edge layouts, and Android 15 specifically changed how this works by default. and set those fill options on the Image to ensure it stretches across the entire screen without constraints.","outputTokens":1408,"requestId":"100F:1E23:30C720:38F2B5:69FD3744"},"id":"3bb85f35-df80-41b0-81f1-e910b619e8de","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:07:43.123Z","parentId":"868464b1-7fae-42ea-9465-bdd4af6e2f79"}
